        "type": "GeneralText",
        "content": "<p>The Bachelor of Arts in Communications requires a minimum of 120 units. The Communications major totals 45 units: 24 units of core requirements; and 21 units in a chosen concentration. In addition, students must complete a minimum of 12 units, earned through a Department of Communications certificate, a minor outside the department or approved coursework outside the department. All Department of Communications prerequisite courses must be completed with a \u201cC\u201d (2.0) or better. Students must earn a minimum of 72 units outside the Department of Communications, plus must meet University General Education requirements. IMPORTANT: The Accrediting Council on Education in Journalism and Mass Communications has set forth strict guidelines for majors in communications. It is imperative that you see the CSU Fullerton catalog under \"Department of Communications,\" \"Bachelor of Arts in Communications\" for additional requirements.</p>",
